# Competitive launch north star

**Full matrix:** [`docs/vision/COMPETITIVE_LAUNCH_ASSESSMENT.md`](../../docs/vision/COMPETITIVE_LAUNCH_ASSESSMENT.md)

## Position

SSTracker wins on **development OS + SafeSport/COPPA architecture**. We lose parent daily-use wars until **RSVP, registration-lite, and mobile/push** ship.

## Moat (extend — do not trade away)

- Player Train → XP → coach intent/bounties → RL homework
- Household-gated comms (no coach→minor unsupervised DM)
- VPC/consent records + minor retention
- Coach spatial drills + three-tier drill library
- **Tryout lifecycle OS** — registration through callback/roster with eval plans + automated comms (see **LAUNCH-tryouts-os**)

## Table stakes (close before launch QA)

1. **LAUNCH-household-graph** — guardian on admin/coach/global users roster (deploy `compliance` CF to dev)
2. **LAUNCH-rsvp** — pre-event going/not/maybe (TeamSnap Premium parity)
3. **LAUNCH-registration-lite** — club program + parent pay (SE/GotSport minimum)
4. **LAUNCH-roster-invite** — name-only athlete → guardian invite
5. **LAUNCH-tryouts-os** — tryout registration → field sessions → check-in → eval plan → callbacks → roster (club moat; phased A–E in ROADMAP)

## Reject for launch scope

- Live streaming, website builder, NGB export (unless owner reopens soccer GTM)
- Player OS visual research / avatar PNG tracks
- QA checklists for broken linkage — fix product first

## Sprint discipline

- One **LAUNCH-*** slice per session; cite wave from assessment doc
- New features must map to matrix row (parity vs moat)
- After household/RSVP changes: `npm run deploy:compliance` or `deploy:core` as documented in [`docs/FUNCTIONS_DEPLOY.md`](../../docs/FUNCTIONS_DEPLOY.md)

## Competitors (quick reference)

| Platform | They win on | We beat them on |
|----------|-------------|-----------------|
| TeamSnap ONE | Parent mobile, RSVP, reg, streaming | Development loop, compliance depth |
| SportsEngine HQ | Eligibility matrix, NGB, enterprise reg | Player OS, SafeSport comms model |
| GotSport | State roster/governing body | Gamified development, RL, intent engine |
